snippet.textDisplay: Man, to be honest, this episode was pretty disappointing. I watch Unraveled because I want a quick laugh, but this just wasn't very funny. Instead, it was a genuine, heartwarming story about the importance of friends, a wholesome narrative that managed to touch on the single thing of any value whatsoever in this crazy, incomprehensible, and painfully brief existence we share together. Which is obviously not as good as being funny.
